node.text:
Always living in the moment 💜 
Are you a dog or cat person? Swipe to see these @nature spots in the four seasons and save this post to visit with your pet! 📝

1. Grand Canyon National Park, Arizona
2. Zion National Park, Utah
3. Bishop, California
4. Golden Gate Bridge, California
5. Sand Harbor Beach, Lake Tahoe, Nevada
6. Chino Hills State Park, California
7. San Francisco, California
8. Point Reyes National Seashore, California
9, 10. San Diego, California

Which seasonal picture is your favorite? 1-10?👇

📽 @sterlingsilvercat #nature

node.text:
Autumn walks in Finland 🍁✨ Have you visited this country in the fall season before?

Fall leaf colours, also known as "Ruska" to locals, characterises this season months in Finland. Landscapes are painted in vivid yellows, reds and browns, making every walk and hike even more magical.

Which picture is your favorite? Tag someone who loves @nature!

📷 @jukkarisikko #nature
📍Finland

node.text:
Hippos have the ability to lock their jaws at nearly 180 degree angles 😍 This feature, which makes a hippo look like it's yawning, is particularly important when hippos end up in conflict with other animals. The wide opening angle means that hippos can produce a bite force of 1,800 PSI—enough to break bones and snap wooden planks in two.

📽 @cincinnatizoo #nature

node.text:
Would you dare? 🦈 When “all the sharks align” and you know you’re in the right place at the right time and years and years of work and experience all come together for an opportunity to experience the very best wildlife experience @nature can offer. 

Magical moments in the deep blue with “Grandma Great White” My great-grandmother used to swim off the south shore of Oahu everyday till she died, “Grandma great white” featured here is actually larger than “Deep Blue” who was around the day before this footage. I’ve been swimming with sharks my whole life and working professionally with them for almost 20 yrs. There’s a challenge I have in my efforts to find a balance between helping people to overcome their fear of sharks that often stems from fictitious media, and instilling a healthy level of respect for sharks. I reached the decision, long ago, to devote the rest of my life to conservation, research, and education. I hope my efforts inspire action for conservation and compassion for heavily misunderstood apex predators and other important marine life. I also hope that it means that more beautiful sharks like this will be saved from wasteful finning for sharks fin soup, shark fishing, or other wasteful things like shark nets, bycatch from industrial longline fleets, or even the pharmaceutical and souvenir trade. 

🤿 @oceanramsey
📽 @juansharks Edited by @jarebutter
@oneoceandiving #nature
🎶 AURORA - Runaway

Squad goals 🙌 Skydiving, is a method of transiting from a high point in the atmosphere to the surface of Earth with the aid of gravity, involving the control of speed during the descent using a parachute or parachutes.

For human skydiving, it may involve a phase of more or less free-falling (the skydiving segment) which is a period when the parachute has not yet been deployed and the body gradually accelerates to terminal velocity.

Have you ever skydive or would you like to try? ☁️

📽 @hepilots #nature

node.text:
Postcards from Turkey 🍃 Have you ever been to this beautiful country before?

Turkey has 44 National Parks that look after its stunning natural heritage – so if you decide to visit, you’ll have plenty of options to choose from (some of our favorites are the Yedigoller National Park and the Saklikent Milli Park). 🌳🇹🇷

Tag a @nature lover! 😍

📷 @cumacevikphoto #nature
📍Turkey
